[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>I am seeking assistance with setting up a Rust for Linux development environment. I noticed there used to be a \"Mentorship Session: Setting Up an Environment for Writing Linux Kernel Modules in Rust\", which provided guidance on this topic; however, it seems to have expired and does not work successfully with the current rust-next branch.</p>\n<p>Additionally, I have read the quick start documentation for Rust for Linux, but unfortunately, I find it lacks the level of detail I need. Could you please let me know if there are any similar, more detailed tutorials available that cover the entire process from cloning the Git repository?</p>\n<p>Thank you for your help!</p>",
        "id": 480673858,
        "sender_full_name": "wenzhao",
        "timestamp": 1730798284
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think there is. But you can ask questions here.</p>",
        "id": 480674426,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1730798474
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>all right, now I have finish the rust support and the compile linux kernel is ready. I want to run my linux kernel in QEMU, however when I try to use busybox it meet the following error:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">lwz</span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"n\">lwz</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">ThinkStation</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">P3</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Tower</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"o\">~/</span><span class=\"n\">github</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"cp\">$</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">allnoconfig</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">qemu</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">busybox</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">min</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span>\n<span class=\"p\">#</span>\n<span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">configuration</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">written</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span>\n<span class=\"p\">#</span>\n<span class=\"n\">scripts</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kconfig</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">109</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">qemu</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">busybox</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">min</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">fragment</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">does</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exists</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">on</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">architecture</span><span class=\"err\">。</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">停止。</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">686</span><span class=\"err\">：</span><span class=\"n\">qemu</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">busybox</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">min</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">错误</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lwz</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">github</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">347</span><span class=\"err\">：</span><span class=\"n\">__build_one_by_one</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">错误</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">224</span><span class=\"err\">：</span><span class=\"n\">__sub</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">错误</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 480689836,
        "sender_full_name": "wenzhao",
        "timestamp": 1730803118
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>this command can run successfully in \"rust\" branch, but it meet error in \"rust-next\" branch. So, how to run the linux kernel in this situation?</p>",
        "id": 480690794,
        "sender_full_name": "wenzhao",
        "timestamp": 1730803434
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I use</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x86_64_defconfig</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">j8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>and the result runs with QEMU system emulation</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">qemu</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">system</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">arch</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">boot</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">bzImage</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">nographic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">append</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"console=ttyS0\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(<code>qemu-system-x86_64</code> might be Ubuntu specific?)</p>\n<p>The <code>x86_64_defconfig</code> doesn't have CONFIG_RUST enabled, though. So you need to enable that.</p>",
        "id": 480697931,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirk Behme",
        "timestamp": 1730805808
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i am not sure what happened. but with the command</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">qemu</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">system</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">arch</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">boot</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">bzImage</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">nographic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">append</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"console=ttyS0\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>my  qemu shows nothing. however with the command</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">qemu</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">system</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">arch</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">boot</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">bzImage</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>my qemu shows the following message:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">end</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Kernel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">panic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">syncing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">VFS</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">unable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mount</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">fs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">on</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"\"</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unknown</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">block</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 480856680,
        "sender_full_name": "wenzhao",
        "timestamp": 1730877024
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"720323\">wenzhao</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/Rust-next.20environment.20setup.20help/near/480856680\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>with the command</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">qemu</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">system</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">arch</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">boot</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">bzImage</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>my qemu shows the following message:</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">end</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Kernel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">panic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">syncing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">VFS</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">unable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mount</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">fs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">on</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"\"</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unknown</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">block</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>First of all, good that it works for you, now <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f642\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span> </p>\n<p>The</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">end</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Kernel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">panic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">syncing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">VFS</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">unable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mount</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">fs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">on</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"\"</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unknown</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">block</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>is expected as we have given no root file system. So your kernel boots but doesn't find any root file system/ user space. If you just want to test compiled in code or for example running the Rust tests this is sufficient, already. Anyhow, you can add a root file system (image) of your choice with the additional QEMU option <code>-initrd</code>. I found <a href=\"https://www.berrange.com/posts/2023/03/09/make-tiny-image-py-creating-tiny-initrds-for-testing-qemu-or-linux-kernel-userspace-behaviour/\">this</a> helpful, but there are many, many root file system image options out there. Choose what you need <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f642\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 480858523,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirk Behme",
        "timestamp": 1730878009
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ok, thanks for your help, I can run the rust-next system now. I enable the \"minimal\" rust module, i saw the following message, and i thought it is ok, right?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">..............................</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mf\">0.571598</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">usbcore</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">registered</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">interface</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">driver</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">usbhid</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mf\">0.571887</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">usbhid</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">USB</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">HID</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">driver</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mf\">0.572118</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_minimal</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Rust</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">minimal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sample</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mf\">0.572373</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_minimal</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Am</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">built</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kc\">true</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mf\">0.572651</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Initializing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">XFRM</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">netlink</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">socket</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mf\">0.572878</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NET</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Registered</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PF_INET6</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">protocol</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">family</span>\n<span class=\"o\">..................................</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mf\">1.044288</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mount</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">51</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">used</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">greatest</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">stack</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">depth</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">14048</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bytes</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">left</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mf\">1.044679</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mount</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">52</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">used</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">greatest</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">stack</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">depth</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">13864</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bytes</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">left</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mf\">1.045287</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">53</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">used</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">greatest</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">stack</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">depth</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">13328</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bytes</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">left</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">Boot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">took</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">1.00</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">seconds</span>\n\n<span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">bin</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">sh</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">can</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">access</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tty</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">job</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">control</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">turned</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">off</span>\n<span class=\"o\">~</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">#</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
